  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>estimate the disease progression rate</measure>
    <time_frame>4 years</time_frame>
    <description>Therefore, in order to ensure that we will have at least 300 patients with PTC being followed with active surveillance, we plan to enroll 325 total patients, of which 228 will have FNA diagnostic for PTC (of which 99% are expected to have PTC) and 97 patients will have FNA suspicious for PTC (of which 73 would be expected to have PTC). This sample size will enable us to estimate the 5 year disease progression rate requiring intervention to within Â±4% at 95% confidence level (using binomial calculation under the assumption that the study is not stopped early and the progression rate is not higher than 10%).</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <number_of_groups>1</number_of_groups>
